			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Soil sampling is a process used to measure various soil characteristics, including chemical, biological, and physical properties. It provides valuable insights into soil health and crop system conditions. Soil microbial activity is a key element that can be assessed through soil testing. Soil samples can be collected at any time of the year, but it is best to avoid extremely wet conditions. The frequency of soil testing depends on the crop and cultivation intensity, ranging from annually to every 2 to 3 years. Grid sampling and zone sampling are two common methods used for collecting soil samples.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">土壤取样是一种用于测量各种土壤特性的过程，包括化学、生物和物理特性。用于洞察土壤健康和作物系统生长条件。土壤微生物活性是一个关键因素，可以通过土壤测试进行评估。土壤样本可以在一年中的任何时候采集，但最好避免极端潮湿的条件。土壤测试的频率取决于作物和种植强度，从每年到每2到3年进行一次。网格采样和区域采样是采集土壤样本的两种常用方法。</common:generalComment>
